<h1><abbr title="Extensible HyperText Markup Language">XHTML</abbr>
namespace</h1>

<p>The namespace name <tt>http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml</tt> is intended for use
in various specifications such as:</p>

<p>Recommendations:</p>
<ul>
  <li><cite><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1"><abbr>XHTML</abbr>â„¢ 1.0:
    The Extensible HyperText Markup Language</a></cite></li>
  <li><cite><a
    href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-modularization"><abbr>XHTML</abbr>
    Modularization</a></cite></li>
  <li><cite><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11"><abbr>XHTML</abbr>
    1.1</a></cite></li>
  <li><cite><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-basic"><abbr>XHTML</abbr>
    Basic</a></cite> </li>
  <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-print/"><cite>XHTML
  Print</cite></a></li>
  <li><a
  href="http://www.w3.org/TR/rdfa-syntax/"><cite>XHTML+RDFa</cite></a></li>
</ul>

<p>Working drafts:</p>
<ul>
  <li><cite><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/html5/">HTML 5: A vocabulary and
    associated APIs for HTML and XHTML</a></cite></li>
</ul>

<p>The charters of the following W3C Working Groups include work on HTML that
may impact this namespace: </p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/2006/07/SWD/">Semantic Web Deployment Working
    Group</a>, chartered July 2006 to work on RDFa</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/PF/">WAI Protocols and Formats Working
    Group (PFWG)</a>, chartered Dec 2006 to work on Accessibility of Dynamic
    Web Content</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/html/wg/">HTML Working Group</a>, chartered
    March 2007</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/MarkUp/">XHTML2 Working Group</a>, chartered
    March 2007</li>
</ul>

<p>For more information about <abbr>XML</abbr> namespaces, please refer to
<cite><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml-names">Namespaces in
<abbr>XML</abbr></a></cite>.</p>
